cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Speech and Dialogue (cs.SD) as it deals with phone recognition from raw speech. Additionally, it could also belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL) as it involves natural language processing. The use of convolutional neural networks suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The fine-tuning of the filterbanks suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Signal Processing (cs.SI). Finally, the use of neural networks for end-to-end phone recognition suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
